Anything (var) resembling a pointer (aka, that can be passed to print_pointer) that is written to an ostream after a LIBCWD_USING_OSTREAM_PRELUDE should be written as-if `<< print_pointer(var)` was used. Likewise, a var of type `bool` should be printed as-if `<< std::boolalpha << var` was used. Likewise, a var that is an enum or enum class should be written as-if `<< to_string(var)` had been used.
